Right now your bot will only be online if your code is running. To keep your coding running I would recommend [Heroku](https://www.heroku.com/), which is a free hosting service and works really well. There are plenty of tutorials online explaining how to host your bot there.

As for your second issue, your bot doesn&#39;t know when to load the commands. You have it upsert commands during start-up.

There are two ways of adding commands.
1) **A guild command** - This command will be added into Discord instantly! The downside is that it is limited to only a 100 commands and is added per guild.

2) **A global command** - This command will be added throughout Discord. As long as your bot is in a server, that server will get the command. You can add unlimited commands. Downside is it might take up to an hour or maybe even more to add.

So to add commands it is very simple. We will use two events.

**Guild Commands:**
```
@Override
public void onGuildReady(@NotNull GuildReadyEvent event) {
    List&lt;CommandData&gt; commandData = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
    commandData.add(Commands.slash(&quot;w2g&quot;, &quot;A test command&quot;));
    event.getGuild().updateCommands().addCommands(commandData).queue();
}
```
This is a simple command handler for a guild command. Every time you create a new command, just add it here. The steps for creating a global command are nearly identical.

**Global Commands:**
```
@Override
public void onReady(@NotNull ReadyEvent event) {
    List&lt;CommandData&gt; commandData = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
    commandData.add(Commands.slash(&quot;w2g&quot;, &quot;A test command&quot;));
    event.getJDA().updateCommands().addCommands(commandData).queue();
}
```
These two methods are different events. The `onGuildReady()` method fires everytime a guild is ready to accept the commands. The `onReady()` method only fires on **bot** start-up.

These are basic command handlers for you to use. If you are creating a much more advanced bot, I would recommend creating a way for you to easily add commands, unpack the command data and add it to Discord.

